  "prompt": "Will there be a sufficient space for rough work in offline mode of JEE?",
  "response": "In the offline mode of the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE), candidates are typically provided with rough work sheets along with the question paper. This allows students to perform calculations, jot down notes, or work through problems as they answer questions.\n\nHowever, specific arrangements can vary, so it's important to check the official guidelines or information released by the National Testing Agency (NTA) or the relevant conducting body for the latest details regarding rough work provisions in the examination. Generally, though, candidates can expect to have enough space for their rough work during the exam.",
